Comment 1: 
A pressing question is why we would price Asian options with deep learning in the first place.
The most common pricing method currently for Asian options (that use arithmetic averages) is 
with monte carlo simulations. The issue with this approach is that many iterations are needed,
and the parameter space needs to be updated repeatedly. Once a deep learning model is trained,
it only needs the current parameter values and will return a predicted value quickly, only 
having to reference its own price distribution.   


