Time to Maturity T - [0.1,2.0] (Years)
Number of Dates to Average n - 12 (monthly), 52 (weekly), and 252 (daily).


Comment 3: 
Now we need to address how we will generate our data. Two viable methods are with uniform sampling
from each parameter range, and Latin hypercube sampling (LHS). LHS is just going to ensure that we more
thoroughly fill the space, as with six dimensions it is not clear how many samples it will take for 
the uniform approach to do the same. 

We will also start by generating 100k sample options, but may increase this number in future iterations.
Due to the relative niceness and simplicity of the problem, we may not need the huge amount of data that 
deep learning is known for.


